
# Privacy Policy

**Effective Date:** March 24, 2026

This Privacy Policy explains how the TBD-Bot Discord bot ("the Bot") collects, uses, and stores information from users who interact with the Bot on Discord servers.

## Information We Collect

- **Transcript Text:** The Bot transcribes and stores only the text of conversations that occur in voice channels where the Bot is active.
- **Discord Username:** The Bot stores the Discord username (e.g., User#1234) of participants for attribution in transcripts.
- **Discord User ID (Optional):** By default, the Bot does not collect or store Discord user IDs. However, server administrators may enable this feature. If enabled, Discord user IDs will be stored for attribution and administrative purposes. This setting is configurable by the server owner.

**No audio recordings or raw audio data are ever saved or retained.**

## How We Use Information

- To provide transcription services and generate text transcripts for server administrators and users.
- To attribute transcript text to the correct Discord username (and, if enabled, Discord user ID).

## Data Storage and Security

- Transcripts are stored as text files or in a database, accessible only to authorized server administrators or as configured by the server owner.
- No audio files are stored. Discord user IDs are only stored if the feature is enabled by the server owner.
- Reasonable security measures are in place to protect stored transcript data from unauthorized access.

## Data Retention

- Transcript text, usernames, and (if enabled) user IDs are retained only as long as necessary for the operation of the Bot or as configured by the server owner.
- Users or server administrators may request deletion of transcript data by contacting the Bot owner.

## Transcription Processing

- All transcription is performed locally using the vibe-transcriber package and/or a self-hosted Vibe API. No transcript data is sent to third-party or external services for processing.

## User Rights

- Users may request access to, correction of, or deletion of their transcript data by contacting the Bot owner.
- Users may remove the Bot from their server at any time to stop all data collection.

## Children’s Privacy

- The Bot is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe such information has been collected, please contact the Bot owner for prompt removal.

## Changes to This Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted in this document with an updated effective date.

## Contact

For questions or requests regarding your data, please contact the Bot owner or administrator as listed in the Bot's profile or documentation.
